{
  "bio": [
    "Annika Bootsman Kleberg is a Swedish shipping heir and co-owner of Soya Group, a multi-billion dollar family conglomerate.",
    "She is the granddaughter of Olof Wallenius, who founded the group in 1934.",
    "The family's wealth stems primarily from shipping, including a major stake in Wallenius Wilhelmsen, one of the world's largest car carriers.",
    "The group has diversified into real estate, wind-propulsion technology, forestry and horse breeding.",
    "She owns 50% of the Soya Group, with the remaining stake held by her brother, Jonas Kleberg."
  ],
  "about": [
    "The family company is named \"Soya\" because the founder's first vessels in the 1930s were converted to carry soybean oil, a pioneering move at the time.",
    "Bootsman Kleberg has a passion for reining, the dressage discipline of Western riding."
  ]
}